  preview={studentfinance2025.png},
  abstract={Using survey experiments in six countries, we find that immigrant students are judged as less deserving of financial aid than natives. High-achieving immigrants can overcome this penalty, but working harder does not help. The immigrant penalty is driven by right-wing voters, while left-leaning respondents treat immigrants equally.}
